AB  - This paper analyzes the value of voting power of Swiss firms which usually issue high-voting- rights stock, low-voting-rights stock, and non-voting stock. Two variables measuring voting- power-inequality are constructed. They are both useful in explaining the voting-rights-premia. Also, the allocation of the voting rights is analyzed. It is shown that majority shareholders hold the high-voting-rights stock.
